data.text: @AfriCryptoklap @thehowie Yes- absolutely. Check out “this week in Virology”. The virus can suppress aspects from the immune system. Vaccination provides greater protection than infection. Each infectious course can be different- one mild case doesn’t mean infection will be mild in the future
@bibty78 @thehowie Didn’t they stop all covid protocols? Does that include testing?
@ellimills10 Not clear. Waning immunity probably dominating other reasons but it may not be just that.
@thehowie Why are cases and hospitalizations rising in England?

@thehowie I’m in NYC. I can’t  speak to hospitalizations, but all the recent +Covid cases among my friends/acquaintances ( and there have been several) were picked up on rapid home tests and subsequently not reported - how trustworthy is the data?
@thehowie CT hospitalization also inching up. With masks off, we were bound to see an uptick.
@thehowie Daily positivity across the state is under 2% today
